ğŸ“¦ Quick Installation Commands
Option 1: Minimal Installation (Core Features Only)
For Google Colab or basic usage:
bashpip install scikit-learn pandas numpy matplotlib seaborn imbalanced-learn joblib Flask Flask-CORS
Option 2: Standard Installation (Recommended)
For full functionality:
bashpip install -r requirements.txt
Option 3: Development Installation
With testing and development tools:
bashpip install -r requirements.txt
pip install pytest black flake8 pytest-cov

ğŸ¯ Simplified requirements.txt (Copy this if you want minimal setup)
Create a file called requirements-minimal.txt:
txt# Core ML Libraries
scikit-learn>=1.3.0
pandas>=2.0.0
numpy>=1.24.0

# Visualization
matplotlib>=3.7.0
seaborn>=0.12.0

# Imbalanced Data
imbalanced-learn>=0.11.0

# Model Storage
joblib>=1.3.0

# Web Framework
Flask>=2.3.0
Flask-CORS>=4.0.0

# Network Analysis (optional)
scapy>=2.5.0

# Utilities
tqdm>=4.65.0
colorama>=0.4.6

ğŸš€ Installation Steps
For Google Colab:
python# Run this in a Colab cell
!pip install scikit-learn pandas numpy matplotlib seaborn imbalanced-learn joblib
For Local Machine:
bash# Step 1: Create virtual environment
python -m venv venv

# Step 2: Activate virtual environment
# On Windows:
venv\Scripts\activate

# On Linux/Mac:
source venv/bin/activate

# Step 3: Upgrade pip
pip install --upgrade pip

# Step 4: Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Or minimal install:
pip install scikit-learn pandas numpy matplotlib seaborn imbalanced-learn joblib Flask Flask-CORS

ğŸ”§ Troubleshooting Installation Issues
Issue 1: Permission Denied
bashpip install --user -r requirements.txt
Issue 2: Slow Installation
bashpip install -r requirements.txt --no-cache-dir
Issue 3: Package Conflicts
bash# Create fresh environment
python -m venv fresh_venv
source fresh_venv/bin/activate  # or venv\Scripts\activate on Windows
pip install -r requirements.txt
Issue 4: C++ Compiler Errors (Windows)

Install Visual C++ Build Tools: https://visualstudio.microsoft.com/visual-cpp-build-tools/

Issue 5: macOS Installation Issues
bashxcode-select --install
pip install -r requirements.txt

ğŸ“Š Verify Installation
After installation, verify everything works:
python# Run this Python script to verify
import sys

packages = {
    'sklearn': 'scikit-learn',
    'pandas': 'pandas',
    'numpy': 'numpy',
    'matplotlib': 'matplotlib',
    'seaborn': 'seaborn',
    'imblearn': 'imbalanced-learn',
    'joblib': 'joblib',
    'flask': 'Flask'
}

print("Checking installed packages...\n")

for module, package in packages.items():
    try:
        exec(f"import {module}")
        version = eval(f"{module}.__version__")
        print(f"âœ… {package:20s} - Version {version}")
    except ImportError:
        print(f"âŒ {package:20s} - NOT INSTALLED")

print("\nPython version:", sys.version)

ğŸ’¾ Save This to File
